                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Curacao</placeName>\n                <date>1 Nov. 1849</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Mr. Isc Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(5)\">I have before me yr favors<lb/> of <date>31<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi>\n                    July</date> and <date>5<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> Sept</date> both accompanying the\n                Occidents all <add>?</add><lb/> I regret to state I have no new subscribers and I\n                fear the next year<lb/> I shall still loose some of the few I have however I must\n                hope<lb/> things will be better then nor have I been more lucky with<lb/> the prayer\n                books, the <sic>hollidays</sic> are always the time to sell but<lb/> not a single\n                sell could I get off all alluding the books are<lb/> too heavy particularly the\n                    <date>kipoor</date>, we have the service<lb/> recd from\n                    <placeName>England</placeName> in 3 Books which are much admired<lb/> every boy\n                wants of that sort, please send me 2 Dz each of the<lb/> Road to faith &amp; Hebrew\n                spelling books they are wanted for the Sunday<lb/> School</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have just Recd a letter from my correspondent in\n                    <placeName>Boston</placeName> who<lb/> informs me he recd the <add>Hebrew</add>\n                of Palm leafs and Citrons and frwa<add>?</add><lb/> them to you but he does not say\n                when I hope they arrived in time<lb/> and proved good <add>?</add> answer to my\n                    <sic>enquiry</sic>, <persName>Miss Joseph Trull</persName><lb/>\n                <add>?</add> inform me that 15 f<add>?</add> were worth 94 c <add>?</add></p>\n            <p rend=\"The final words on the page are obscured by a sticker.\"/>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p30p0xb2h/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
